body:
> Also, IMHO, you should add the config to the default Drill config so that people can query `ltsv` files by default.

Is it correct to add `bootstrap-storage-plugins.json` into format-ltsv/src/main/resources? I tried adding `bootstrap-storage-plugins.json`, but it didn't work.
Like this.
```
{
  "storage": {
    dfs: {
      type: "ltsv",
      connection: "file:///",
      formats: {
      "ltsv": {
        "type": "ltsv",
        "extensions": [ "ltsv" ]
      },
      enabled: true
    }
  }
}
```

@shimamoto , 
I think it is good to add the ltsv to the `bootstrap.json` file.  If you're stuck on the unit tests, take a look  here: https://github.com/apache/drill/blob/27d6505d73f2c18e6a87c580f402ed12b5955f97/contrib/format-syslog/src/test/java/org/apache/drill/exec/store/syslog/TestSyslogFormat.java

What questions do you have re: default Drill config?

@vvysotskyi, I addressed your comments. Also, I regenerated protobufs and modified travis.yml to use version 3.6.0. It will generate protobuf deb package and cache it for later reuse.
Note that the protobufs are still using syntax proto2. Updating to proto3 will require deeper investigation and most likely significant changes in code and approach. I'll create a new JIRA ticked for that.
Could you please review?
